Normalization Report: Library Management System:

First Normal Form (1NF)
    Created books, authors, members, copies, loans tables
    No multi-valued attributes.
    Each columns holds atomic values.
    Unique primary keys defined for all table.

Second Normal Form (2NF)
    book_authors table introduced with composite PK to avoid storing multiple authors directly in books
    Every non-key attribute is fully dependent on the whole primary key.
    No partial dependency remains.

Third Normal Form (3NF)
    Moved publisher_name from books into new table publishers
    Replaced staff_name in loans with staff_id referencing staff table.
    No non-key attribute depends on another non-key attribute.
    All attributes depend only on the primary key of their table.

FINAL SCHEMA 3NF
  Entities: 
      publishers, books, authors, book_authors, members, copies, loans, staff.
  Benefits:
      Data redundancy reduced.
      Referential integrity maintained through foreign keys.
      Anomalies (update, insertion, deletion) removed.
